181.4	Portuguese_language	Portuguese language	Portuguese or língua portuguesa) is a Romance language. It is the official language of Portugal, the former South American Portuguese colony of Brazil and former colonies in Africa: Mozambique, Angola, Cape Verde, Guiné-Bissau and São Tomé e Príncipe. Portuguese has co-official status (alongside the indigenous language) in Macao, and in East Timor in South East Asia; Portuguese speakers are also found in Goa in India.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Map_of_the_portuguese_language_in_the_world.png/300px-Map_of_the_portuguese_language_in_the_world.png
